        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 12:40PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 1240 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mouse Trap Butte, or 22 miles southeast of Rome, moving northeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust reducing
visibilities. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Mouse Trap Butte and Grassy Mountain around 1250 PM MDT.
Castro Ridge around 110 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
